  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements in many countries for reporting suspected money laundering. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to:\n\n1. Have internal anti-money laundering (AML) policies\n2. Report suspicious transactions to financial intelligence units\n3. Conduct customer due diligence\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering activities\n\nThe specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but most developed countries have similar frameworks.",
